Date: Thu, 19 Aug 2021 17:37:02 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: broadcom: bcm4908: Fix UART clock name
Mime-version: 1.0
Content-type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-transfer-encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 6c38c39ab2141f53786d73e706675e8819a3f2cb
Patch-mainline: v5.16-rc1
References: stable-5.14.19

[ Upstream commit 6c38c39ab2141f53786d73e706675e8819a3f2cb ]

According to the binding the correct clock name is "refclk".

Fixes: 2961f69f151c ("arm64: dts: broadcom: add BCM4908 and Asus GT-AC5300 early DTS files")
Signed-off-by: Rafał Miłecki <rafal@milecki.pl>
Signed-off-by: Florian Fainelli <f.fainelli@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm4908/bcm4908.dtsi | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm4908/bcm4908.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm4908/bcm4908.dtsi
index a5a64d17d9ea..f6b93bbb4922 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm4908/bcm4908.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm4908/bcm4908.dtsi
@@ -292,7 +292,7 @@ uart0: serial@640 {
 			reg = <0x640 0x18>;
 			interrupts = <GIC_SPI 32 IRQ_TYPE_LEVEL_HIGH>;
 			clocks = <&periph_clk>;
-			clock-names = "periph";
+			clock-names = "refclk";
 			status = "okay";
 		};
 
